comment:
* Parcelable object to handle call quality. *

* Currently this supports IMS calls. *

* It provides the call quality level, duration, and additional information related to RTP packets, * jitter and delay. *

* If there are multiple active calls, the CallQuality will pertain to the call in the foreground. * * @hide

variables.name: CALL_QUALITY_EXCELLENT
variables.comment: Constants representing the call quality level (see #CallQuality);

methods.name: public int getDownlinkCallQualityLevel()
methods.comment: * Returns the downlink CallQualityLevel for a given ongoing call.

methods.name: public int getUplinkCallQualityLevel()
methods.comment: * Returns the uplink CallQualityLevel for a given ongoing call.

methods.name: public int getCallDuration()
methods.comment: * Returns the duration of the call, in milliseconds.

methods.name: public int getNumRtpPacketsTransmitted()
methods.comment: * Returns the total number of RTP packets transmitted by this device for a given ongoing call.

methods.name: public int getNumRtpPacketsReceived()
methods.comment: * Returns the total number of RTP packets received by this device for a given ongoing call.

methods.name: public int getNumRtpPacketsTransmittedLost()
methods.comment:
* Returns the number of RTP packets which were sent by this device but were lost in the
     * network before reaching the other party.

methods.name: public int getNumRtpPacketsNotReceived()
methods.comment:
* Returns the number of RTP packets which were sent by the other party but were lost in the
     * network before reaching this device.

methods.name: public int getAverageRelativeJitter()
methods.comment:
* Returns the average relative jitter in milliseconds. Jitter represents the amount of variance * in interarrival time of packets, for example, if two packets are sent 2 milliseconds apart * but received 3 milliseconds apart, the relative jitter between those packets is 1 * millisecond. * *

See RFC 3550 for more information on jitter calculations.

methods.name: public int getMaxRelativeJitter()
methods.comment:
* Returns the maximum relative jitter for a given ongoing call. Jitter represents the amount of * variance in interarrival time of packets, for example, if two packets are sent 2 milliseconds * apart but received 3 milliseconds apart, the relative jitter between those packets is 1 * millisecond. * *

See RFC 3550 for more information on jitter calculations.

methods.name: public int getAverageRoundTripTime()
methods.comment: * Returns the average round trip time in milliseconds.

methods.name: public boolean isRtpInactivityDetected()
methods.comment: * Returns true if no rtp packets are received continuously for the last 4 seconds

methods.name: public boolean isIncomingSilenceDetectedAtCallSetup()
methods.comment:
* Returns true if only silence rtp packets are received for a duration of 20 seconds starting
     * at call setup

methods.name: public boolean isOutgoingSilenceDetectedAtCallSetup()
methods.comment:
* Returns true if only silence rtp packets are sent for a duration of 20 seconds starting at
      * call setup

methods.name: public int getCodecType()
methods.comment:

     * @see ImsStreamMediaProfile#AUDIO_QUALITY_GSM_EFR
     * @see ImsStreamMediaProfile#AUDIO_QUALITY_GSM_FR
     * @see ImsStreamMediaProfile#AUDIO_QUALITY_GSM_HR
     * @see ImsStreamMediaProfile#AUDIO_QUALITY_G711U
     * @see ImsStreamMediaProfile#AUDIO_QUALITY_G723
     * @see ImsStreamMediaProfile#AUDIO_QUALITY_G711A
     * @see ImsStreamMediaProfile#AUDIO_QUALITY_G722

     * @see ImsStreamMediaProfile#AUDIO_QUALITY_G729
